## M22.1(1/8): resource-RETURNING call result used as anonymous temporary is rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 39 post-implementation review: the
## structural-only check (`(share (call ...))`) caught the
## canonical `*Foo(...)` shape but missed function calls whose
## return type is a resource handle (`fun make_user() -> *User`).
## Same leak class — the Rc is allocated by the called function,
## its `.age` is extracted, then the Rc is dropped on the floor
## (strong count stays at 1, allocation never freed).
##
## V1 policy: the M22.1 leak check is two-tiered. The structural
## tier (`isFreshResourceAlloc`) gives a precise diagnostic
## naming the constructor; the type-aware tier (post-synth
## `isResourceOwningType` on a `(call ...)` result) covers
## resource-returning functions with a generic diagnostic.
## Both reject the same hazard.

struct User
  age: Int

fun make_user() -> *User
  return *User(age: 5)

sub main()
  a = make_user().age   # error: resource-valued call result anonymous
  print(a)
